}

^["stream"]{
 >>[2026-04-16 11:02] observe — the base token layer is still very warm and paper-heavy, which forces route surfaces to compensate with their own local palettes instead of inheriting a stable system.
 >>[2026-04-16 11:05] observe — shared materials, shell cards, and image helper chrome still mix against literal white and warm-light fallbacks, so theme changes never fully propagate.
 >>[2026-04-16 11:08] observe — `home`, `topics`, `website`, and `settings` each re-author surface colors in a different dialect; the issue is less "bad route colors" than weak shared balance.
 >>[2026-04-16 11:10] decide — sequence the pass as shared tokens and material surfaces first, then only the route surfaces whose local gradients and panel mixes still overpower the new base.
 >>[2026-04-16 11:12] hygiene — base ref recorded as main@761b833; preserve the existing uncommitted settings/resonance follow-up and avoid unrelated drift in `public/css/services-surface.css`, `public/css/spw-chrome.css`, and `public/js/spw-spells.js`.
 >>[2026-04-16 11:14] taste — this should read as a calmer, more dimensional palette, not a generic desaturation pass.
}

